Get Data

download.file("https://www.getthedata.com/downloads/open_pubs.csv.zip","open_pubs.csv.zip")
unzip("open_pubs.csv.zip")
pubs <- read.csv("open_pubs.csv", header = FALSE)
names(pubs) <- c("ID","Name","Address","ZIP","U1","U2","Lat","Lng","City")
pubs$Lat <- as.numeric(as.character(pubs$Lat))
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
pubs$Lng <- as.numeric(as.character(pubs$Lng))
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion

Map the pubs!

library(leaflet)
pubs %>%
    leaflet() %>%
    addTiles() %>%
    addMarkers(popup = pubs$Name) %>%
#    Removed clustering, as it prevented markers from appearing on initial load
#    addMarkers(popup = pubs$Name, clusterOptions = markerClusterOptions()) %>%
    setView(lng = 0.3, lat = 52.3, zoom = 08)
## Assuming 'Lng' and 'Lat' are longitude and latitude, respectively
